messages.content: **12. Point 8: On Deceit**
Horatius awakens in what looks like some sort of incredibly upscale rich folk rec room. Wress is there, as is a woman holding her head in pain in the corner.

They look around nervously. *What… What just happened? Am I back in Arctica again? Maybe I swapped back just in time to escape from that 'X' bastard… That'd be one hell of a lucky break. But then what's going on here?*
"Wress?"

"Horatius? Thank goodness. Yeah, you're... back with us, I guess is a way to put it." He looks over his shoulder, though nothing is behind him besides a closed door. "Things have kind of gone pear-shaped and off the walls. But I guess that's practically business as usual for us."
They roll their eyes. "What happened this time?”
"Well, Voreverl's back, and somehow I think that's the least of our problems."

He looks over at the woman. "That's new, though. She wasn't like this until just now. You okay, um, lady?"

The woman just groans and swears, allowing Horatius to recognize this as the voice of Katrielle Groverfield.
Horatius immediately stands up and walks towards Katrielle until they're directly in front of her. "*You.* What the fuck are *you* doing here? You've got a lot to answer for."
She stares up at Horatius, her eyes unfocused. "Whh..?"

"Oh, don't give me that." They slap her across the face in an attempt to bring her back to reality. "The last time we spoke, you were acting all high-and-mighty about this big plan you had for keeping my partner's body for your advantage. Now, you're going to explain to me exactly what that was all about."
She screams. "I'm not... this isn't... didn't... gjhghggrk..."
"What, and now you're going to start shrieking and making excuses? I don't have time for this. I thought you knew how to control your womanhood better than that."

She jolts upward, grabbing Horatius by the collar. She's incredibly sweaty and unsteady.

"Fuck... you."

She lets go and collapses to the ground, unconscious.


Wress coughs. "I don't think you're going to be able to get anything out of her right now. Besides, she's... I don't think we have to worry as much about her. She's got a lot of sketchy aims and plans, but she's *sane*. We can trust she won't blow up a whole building with herself in it, or something. That's becoming a more and more exclusive group, it feels like."

Horatius sighs. "That's also a low bar. Well, it was worth a shot, anyway." They start pacing around the room. "As much as I'd like to head straight for wherever Voreverl is right now– and believe me, I will– I should probably get a clearer picture of the situation beyond 'being surrounded by people I hate'." They hesitate for a moment. "…Except you, I mean."

"Thanks." Wress sighs. "So, here's the situation. First, we had some unrelated problems; this woman showed up against our expectations along with Bern's group, some vague suspicion about each other, and a younger recruit of ours, Gratia, has leaked our location. That'll be an issue a few hours from now if we haven't left." He looks from side to side. "I think that's... everything that happened. Before she showed up."

"Then Voreverl takes over the body. And then from a lower part of this building this other girl shows up with a maid? The maid... or, the girl? One of them is named Erica. They're both delusional, but all our men are in that room they've commandeered for their nonsense."

He paces around the room. "Right now, at least the last I saw, there's Voreverl, Furn, Gratia, Erica, the other one who might be Erica, a translucent projection of a man, and a few dozen of our people who have failed to take control of the situation. All in a dining room sort of area. That's most of it."
((Them both pacing around the room together is a funny mental image))

"I… see. Hm." Honestly, they don't want to walk over to that room. Dealing with all that sounds incredibly exhausting. But it'd probably be worse if they just ignored it and let the problems continue to pile up… Such is life. "I guess I'll head there to try to see what I can do for the situation, then. Before I go, though, where do we want to be leaving for? Any particular location in mind, or does just 'anywhere but here' work?"

“Unless you or anyone has an objection, we’ll be off to the capital next. Jorge has already left in the opposite direction for one last diplomatic effort in Prosperiva. His group will rendezvous with us after we’ve fully prepared things for… well, the final battle.”

"Oh." The 'final battle' already? Somehow, it feels like they got to this stage much earlier than expected. Maybe it's because of all the meandering around Wress had done beforehand giving them low expectations, but even then, the goal they've been chasing after for as long as they could remember now being nearly in the palm of their hand feels surreal. No matter their level of commitment to the Gadflies, as long as they accomplish this, anything is possible.
"In that case, I'll certainly try my hardest to make this go well. Regardless of how many ups and downs this path has had, this fight is just as important to me as it is to you. If anything, I'll make it the one battle we don't fuck up somehow."

“There’s a lot left to do, but… we do have people on our side, as insane and distracting as the people who aren’t may be. I’m optimistic.” He gestures to the door, chuckling. “Shall we get this over with?”
"Let's."

Horatius Kyodu heads towards and enters the dining room. The situation is much as Wress described it, with the exception of two things.
- There are now dice on the floor
- There is a Horatius Kyodu who looks like Horatius Kyodu

((have to make the channel))
"What the fuck?" Wress Hifele.
"My banter is way better than yours!"
Horatius makes an incredibly confused expression. After a few seconds of standing still, they reach out to touch the face of the other Horatius to see if they're real.
"Gwehehahahah! I'm surrounded by children with pea-sized brains! You came back!? Really!? It's obvious you're outmatched! So why don't you just go ahead and lay down so I can kill you already!"
"Shut up for a second, okay? Who the hell is this?"
"Hey, don't touch me, fake fake Horatius! This is my rivalry scene with Voreverl, I don't have time to kill you right now." I push away the fake fake Horatius.
"What… the fuck are you doing? Who are you? How do you know me?"
Wress Hifele heads to the wall of the room with a window, fiddling with the curtains.
"I'm Horatius Kyodu, the protagonist. And I know everything." I, Horatius Kyodu, the protagonist, scoff confidently.
"Ugh, this isn't important! It's not my evil scheme, so we don't need to gloat about specifics! I've wasted enough time, we don't know when Horatius will get back, so I have to kill you now!"
"Horatius is here."
"Yeah, that's what I just said." I move out of Voreverl's way.
A man who looks like this is here, FYI.

"I mean the... the person who calls themself Horatius and is in that body!" Voreverl points towards the Horatius who entered this room most recently "I don't have a good way of differentiating them and my rival, okay!?"
"Aha! You said it!" I smirk. "That's right, me and Voreverl are rivals. Officially."

"Are you… making someone else play me so that you can call them your rival and play pretend with them??" Horatius stares incredulously, but the more they take in this information, they begin to start laughing mockingly. "Wow, how pathetic can you get? This is just embarrassing."

Wress successfully opens the window, exposing Erica to direct sunlight, dissipating the illusion. This is a consistent trait of disguise self in universe that has come up at least once before within TAP in someone else's route.
((I confirm.))
"I don't know what you even planned to do with that. Obviously I'd know the real one was the person I'd stayed with." Wress shakes his head.
"Holy shit, you really were! Ahahaha!" They point at Voreverl and laugh again, a little more hysterically. "That's so fucking desperate!"

"I... I didn't make them do anything! They did this on their own! They're the pathetic... I don't have to explain myself to you, you don't even know me! Shut up! I didn't want to be rivals with them!"
"Shut up! This isn't about you 2! This is me and Voreverl! Get out of here!" I rebecome Horatius very quickly as soon as I can.
"...I don't understand. You have already been acknowledged as Voreverl's rival. This is unnecessary." The Maid says this. "You should not bother with an inferior form."

"Oh, sure, whatever you guys say," they relent, still giggling. "I know you two must think you're the center of the world, but I do actually have business with Voreverl, alright? You guys can have your sick fun all you want after this, but she has something I need back."
"Eh- Well, obviously Horatius's form is inferior, but- Well, this form's been used by a lot of inferiors too! I was going to wipe the slate clean!"

"Oh, what is it you need back? Your brains? Your soul? How about your ability to achieve anything? Guess what, asshole, I didn't take any of them! You didn't have them from the start!" Voreverl spits at Horatius "And considering how buddy buddy you're being with your lover, Wress, over there... You're not Kyozou, are you?"
"Who cares what he is? Just kill him, already!"
"Okay." Rene attempts to attack Horatius Kyodu, but is stopped by Wress. They enter the NPCs I don't need to describe for the near future zone as they struggle.

They twitch at the remark about Wress. "Would you quit making such a big fucking deal out of that? I don't know who 'Kyozou' is, and I don't care. You're a sad little girl who needs to put on all these acts to feel more special than anyone else, and honestly, on some level I can respect that. I certainly can't claim to have never wanted to become someone else to make myself feel better. I do it every day." They sigh. "But you just can't keep yourself from fucking even that up. You have to act like everything's this big fight between the heroes and villains, or whatever 'rivals' bullshit you have going on now. What you don't understand is that no one fucking cares about you, and no one is going to pay any more attention to you no matter how special you try to make yourself seem. It'll just make them want to be around you even less." Shaking their head, they conclude, "You're free to stay in your own little world and delude yourself into thinking you're any less cosmically insignificant than you really are. I genuinely could not give less of a shit. It's just… Well, you're in my partner's body right now, and that's someone who actually does matter to me. So if you could find some way to get yourself back in your own, that'd be great! Thanks."

"Not you, Rene! Voreverl is supposed to kill him! And also, for the record, deluding yourself about reality is way cooler than whatever petty bullshit you're on! Me and Voreverl are going to fight for way past your miserable short life!" Madakoe, can you just hurry up with their deaths now?

"Aw, thanks Horatius, I really appreciate the kind words! I'll make sure to take it into consideration as I rip your partner's spine out and dance on his grave! What the hell do you hope to accomplish with this big speech!? I don't give a shit how you see me! I don't give a shit how anyone sees me! I *am* more important than you! I *am* more important than everyone! Stop deluding yourself into thinking your hatred of me is anything other than jealousy! Now if you want to help me get the hell out of this body, why don't you let me finish my little experiment? We'll kill you and see what happens when Kyozou enters your body again!"
"Fuck."
What's wrong?

"I guess I shouldn't have expected you to listen to reason, yeah. It was just worth a try." They shrug. "Seriously though, *what* are you on about with this fuckin' Kyozou guy? Why do you think I'm going to let anyone enter *my* body?"
"We shouldn't be mentioning... I just assumed you guys all wouldn't care. It's... fine. Whatever."

Voreverl looks dumbfounded "You... Wress didn't tell you!? Pffthahahahaha! I'm so happy to be the one to break the news to you! Welcome to my world of misery, Horatius! While you were out, someone else took control of your body! Called themself Kyozou! Everyone here can confirm it!"
They just give a derisive smile back. "Yeah, as if. Wress, she's full of shit, right?"
Madakoe, can you just be clear? Shouldn't be mentioning what? You could be confusing you, I mean- Fuck, I really need to figure this out. I walk out of the room.

Wress recovers from being grappled by Rene who stopped grappling Wress when Erica said no Voreverl is supposed to kill Horatius Rene isn't supposed to kill Horatius.

"I don't know what that's about, Voreverl's just trying to screw with you. You were awake and not quite lucid for a few minutes, but nothing like that." Wress.

"Well at least you understand you're talking to someone of extreme importance. I was just making process on reclaiming my life. When my former ally struck me down! That asshole! I'm gonna rust him until he can't move! Then I'll smelt him down into my throne! I'd prefer one of skulls, but I can settle."
"...Skulls? No, haha..." **He looks confused.** "No, you- you're not me at all. What is your deal? You-you're a bad guy?"

"Gweh... Gweheheh... *A* bad guy? No no, my foolish muscle head. I'm THE bad guy! Number 1! I invented evil itself! Look it up in a dictionary and you'll see an image of me! I bring death and destruction wherever I go! I'm a swarm of locusts all bundled up into a human body ready to feast on anyone in my path! I am Voreverl Leocot! Remember my name well!" Voreverl looks proud of herself "Whew, that was a good one. I needed that."

"Ohhhh you- okay. You're Voreverl. I heard of you." **He sighs, and slouches back down.** "Great. Why- why"

**He turns back a bit.** "It doesn't matter."
"My name's Mr. Big Man Jr. I'm a wrestler, and a hero for justice! I fight bad guys."
"But you don't seem like the other evil people I know, most of them are... different. Most evil people aren't trying to tangle with such a fine warrior. What evil deeds have you done?"

"So my reputation precedes me, as expected. You seem to have failed a bit in your research if you don't even know my exploits, but you have a good intuition! I'm not like other evil people! I'm better than them! They don't even compare to the rotten corrupted soul inside of me! Let me give you just a taste of what I've done! You know the pope? I *stole* his *car*! That's right! The whole car!"
"Do you hate the pope?"

"Wha... Uh, well." Voreverl thinks for a moment "I-I guess? His religion is fucking stupid. I guess I don't have anything against the guy personally. We *are* working together right now... Which just makes me betraying him all the more evil!"
"Did you need a car?"
"I needed *his* car specifically! Whoever drives the popemobile is the pope! That's how it works! It was the quickest way to get legions of followers to do my bidding!"
"...Are you the pope?"
"...Probably not? I mean... I *was* 4 months ago, when I had the car. But, uh, it's probably been returned to him now? I forgot to ask."
"Are you doing any evil things... currently? Are you in the process?"

"Of course! Once I take control of my life, I'll figure out how to control reality! Then I'll destroy it and remake it in my image! Or, something like that. I just had the idea, haven't worked out the specifics. You're kind of catching me at a bad time."
"...Why do you even like... being evil? Why do you do it?"

"Do you ask a gay person why they're gay? I was born this way! I am evil incarnate! That's all there is to it! I don't need a motivation! Sympathetic villains are for losers who can't handle how cool a real villain is!"
"...Okay then, I guess."
"Do you need to go to jail? Do you want- do you want me to send you to jail? Is that why you're admitting this to me?"
Voreverl takes a step back "W-wait are you, like, a cop? Of course I don't want to go to jail again! What villain stays in jail!? How am I supposed to execute my schemes from a cell!?"

"The life of a law enforcement agent is not for me. I serve no persons, only people. No states, only the state... of wellbeing!" **He grins.** "But bad guys go to jail... when they break laws, at least."
"But you... I mean, if you returned the car, and the pope forgave you..."
"It sounds like everything you say that makes you evil is either a wild fantasy or a strange roundabout personal... tomfoolery."
"I fight evildoers both big and small... but... you really don't feel like you need to be smote at all. It almost feels like you're smiting yourself."

Voreverl cringes at this and then starts angrily stomping towards MBMJ until she's in his face "What did you just say!? What... What the hell do you know!? Who even are you!? You can't make a judgement on me! Y-You're just afraid of what would happen if you fought me, that's it! I'm evil! I do evil! I need to be smote because of that! But... but I won't be! Because I'm going to win! Okay!? Got it!? Just... shut up! Okay!?"
**MBMJ smirks at her.** "You want to do something about it, knave? Test your mettle."

Before anything else, Joliene goes looking for Zita. Where she'd usually be. Wherever that it.
She finds a servant stood outside the door to Zita's quarters. "Miss Swansong? Do you need something?"
"Is she here right now? I'd like to speak to her briefly."

"Her Majesty is currently suffering from rather drastic fits and headaches. If you have business with her, it would be better to--"

Zita opens the door, clutching her head, and looks at Joliene. "Come in."
"...Of course." She does so, and closes the door behind herself.
A medicine man nods at Joliene's entrance. He is the one other person in the room. "Yes... are you feeling alright, Joliene?"
Zita asks this, to be clear.
"...I'm doing fine. Physically, I mean. I'm not here to talk to the doctor. I'd just like to apologize for letting... all *that* happen."

"It's fine. You acted rationally and admirably under the circumstances. I think you did, from what I remember. See, ah... You weren't here, the past however long it's been. Around a day, I think. Doctor says your body remained unconscious the whole time, longer than someone would normally spend sleeping. But I... I mean, I suppose it's a good thing, but I was never gone from Arctica. I remember spending the day here and all the work I did... and I also remember leaving and meeting a bunch of odd folk in a false world. It's... quite strenuous." She sighs. "Dextrum, of course, is under intense questioning. Effectively house arrest. But we can't really throw the book at him, so to speak, right now."

"...That's not what I expected to happen to your body here, but I suppose it's not the worst outcome. Definitely odd, though. I was about to ask about Dextrum — I was hoping to talk to him, though I can wait until he's free, I suppose. Regardless, I'll make sure that never happens to you again."
"He's... the 'house arrest' is in his office here. At his own request. And out of necessity. You should be able to speak to him when you get the chance."
